lass=3D"ArticleNewsFeature_sectionContainer__OveP_"><section class=3D"Artic=
leCopy_articleCopy__KY1Qq"><h2>Who can cast the Patronus charm?</h2>
<p><a href=3D"https://www.wizardingworld.com/writing-by-jk-rowling/patronus=
-charm">The Patronus</a> is a form of advanced magic which even the most qu=
alified wizards can struggle with. Harry Potter was one of the youngest wiz=
ards to cast a corporeal Patronus, having been taught by Professor Lupin at=
 the tender age of 13.</p>
<h2>And, erm, what exactly is a Patronus?</h2>
<p>As Professor Lupin told Harry in <em>Prisoner of Azkaban</em>, the Patro=
nus is =E2=80=98a kind of Anti-Dementor =E2=80=93 a guardian which acts as =
a shield between you and the Dementor.=E2=80=99 It=E2=80=99s also =E2=80=98=
a kind of positive force, a projection of the very things that the Dementor=
 feeds upon =E2=80=93 hope, happiness, the desire to survive =E2=80=93 but =
it cannot feel despair, as real humans can, so the Dementors can=E2=80=99t =
hurt it.=E2=80=99</p>
<p>The Patronus has two forms, non-corporeal and corporeal. A non-corporeal=
 Patronus can appear as =E2=80=98a thin wisp of silver=E2=80=99 that hovers=
 =E2=80=98like mist=E2=80=99. Whereas a corporeal Patronus has a form that =
is clearly defined and is more than vapour or smoke.</p>
<p>The ability to cast a corporeal or non-corporeal Patronus is down to the=
 skill of the witch or wizard. Each Patronus is unique to the witch or wiza=
rd who conjures it, and it=E2=80=99s possible, in some cases, for a Patronu=
s to change.</p>
<h2>The witches and wizards who can cast this spell</h2>
<p>Here are the witches and wizards who accomplished it, with some signific=
ant Patronus moments from across the stories.</p>
<p><strong>Harry Potter =E2=80=93 Stag</strong></p>
<blockquote>
<p>Harry flung himself out from behind the bush and pulled out his wand.<br=
>
=E2=80=98EXPECTO PATRONUM!=E2=80=99 he yelled.<br>
And out of the end of his wand burst, not a shapeless cloud of mist, but a =
blinding, dazzling, silver animal. He screwed up his eyes, trying to see wh=
at it was. It looked like a horse.
<br>
<em>Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban</em></p>
</blockquote>
<p>Harry=E2=80=99s Patronus took the same shape as his father=E2=80=99s. He=
 saw it for the first time during a Dementor attack with Hermione and Siriu=
s at the Great Lake, and at first glance it looked like a horse. Coincident=
ally, the Patronus of Harry=E2=80=99s future wife, Ginny, was a horse.</p>
