James Potter=E2=80=99s Patronus was the same form as his Animagus.</p>
<p><strong>Lily Potter =E2=80=93 Doe</strong><br>
The female form of her husband=E2=80=99s Patronus. We later learn that Seve=
rus Snape, in love with Lily for nearly his whole life, also had a doe for =
his Patronus.</p>
<p><strong>Albus Dumbledore =E2=80=93 Phoenix</strong></p>
<blockquote>
<p>=E2=80=98Should I go and get someone?=E2=80=99 said Harry. =E2=80=98Mada=
m Pomfrey?=E2=80=99<br>
=E2=80=98No,=E2=80=99 said Dumbledore swiftly. =E2=80=98Stay here.=E2=80=99=
<br>
He raised his wand into the air and pointed it in the direction of Hagrid=
=E2=80=99s cabin. Harry saw something silvery dart out of it and streak awa=
y through the trees like a ghostly bird.<br>
<em>Harry Potter and the Goblet of Fire</em></p>
</blockquote>
<p>Dumbledore=E2=80=99s Patronus was a phoenix, which was revealed to us wh=
en he wanted to summon Hagrid after Viktor Krum was Stunned. It can be no s=
urprise that Dumbledore had an affinity with this particular creature, give=
n that his own animal companion was an enigmatic and loyal phoenix, Fawkes.=
</p>
<p><strong>Remus Lupin =E2=80=93 Wolf</strong><br>
Remus Lupin often disguised his Patronus so as not to reveal the fact that =
<a href=3D"https://www.wizardingworld.com/writing-by-jk-rowling/werewolves"=
>he was a werewolf.</a></p>
<p><strong>Nymphadora Tonks =E2=80=93 Wolf</strong></p>
<blockquote>
<p>=E2=80=98Tonks=E2=80=99s Patronus has changed its form,=E2=80=99 he told=
 him. =E2=80=98Snape said so, anyway. I didn=E2=80=99t know that could happ=
en. Why would your Patronus change?=E2=80=99<br>
Lupin took his time chewing his turkey and swallowing before saying slowly,=
 =E2=80=98Sometimes =E2=80=A6 a great shock =E2=80=A6 an emotional upheaval=
 =E2=80=A6=E2=80=99<br>
=E2=80=98It looked big, and it had four legs,=E2=80=99 said Harry, struck b=
y a sudden thought and lowering his voice. =E2=80=98Hey =E2=80=A6 it couldn=
=E2=80=99t be =E2=80=93?=E2=80=99
<br>
<em>Harry Potter and the Half-Blood Prince</em></p>
</blockquote>
<p>Yes, Harry, it could. Tonks=E2=80=99s Patronus changed into a wolf after=
 she fell in love with Lupin, a sure sign of true love if ever there was on=
e.</p>
<p><strong>Minerva McGonagall =E2=80=93&nbsp;Cat</strong></p>
<blockquote>
<p>=E2=80=98Come. We must alert the other Heads of House. You=E2=80=99d bet=
ter put that Cloak back on.=E2=80=99<br>
She marched towards the door, and as she did so she raised her wand. From t=
he tip burst three silver cats with spectacle markings around their eyes. T=
he Patronuses ran sleekly ahead, filling the spiral staircase with silvery =
lights, as Professor McGonagall, Harry and Luna hurried back down.
<br>
<em>Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows</em></p>
</blockquote>
<p>Well of course Professor McGonagall could cast a Patronus. It being a sp=
ell of advanced magic, and she being Professor Minerva McGonagall, she coul=
d also cast three at once. Here, McGonagall used her Patronuses for communi=
cation =E2=80=93&nbsp;to alert the Heads of House that Hogwarts would soon =
be under attack from Voldemort, before the Battle of Hogwarts began.</p>
<p><strong>Severus Snape =E2=80=93 Doe</strong></p>
<blockquote>
<p>=E2=80=98For him?=E2=80=99 shouted Snape. =E2=80=98Expecto patronum!=E2=
=80=99<br>
From the tip of his wand burst the silver doe: she landed on the office flo=
or, bounded once across the office and soared out of the window. Dumbledore=
 watched her fly away, and as her silvery glow faded he turned back to Snap=
e, and his eyes were full of tears.<br>
=E2=80=98After all this time?=E2=80=99<br>
=E2=80=98Always,=E2=80=99 said Snape.
<br>
<em>Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows</em></p>
</blockquote>
<p>It still gets <em>us</em> after all this time. We also see Snape=E2=80=
=99s Patronus when it guides Harry to Godric Gryffindor=E2=80=99s sword in =
<em>Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows</em>.</p>
