<p><strong>Cho Chang	=E2=80=93 Swan</strong></p>
<p><strong>Seamus Finnigan	=E2=80=93&nbsp;Fox</strong></p>
<p><strong>Hermione Granger =E2=80=93 Otter</strong></p>
<p><strong>Luna Lovegood	=E2=80=93 Hare</strong></p>
<p><strong>Ernie Macmillan	=E2=80=93&nbsp;Boar</strong></p>
<p><strong>Ginny Weasley =E2=80=93 Horse</strong></p>
<p><strong>Ron Weasley	=E2=80=93 Jack Russell terrier</strong></p>
<p>They were later cast, with varying success and in support of Harry, duri=
ng the Battle of Hogwarts:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>He saw Ron=E2=80=99s silver terrier burst into the air, flicker feebly a=
nd expire; he saw Hermione=E2=80=99s otter twist in mid-air and fade, and h=
is own wand trembled in his hand, and he almost welcomed the oncoming obliv=
ion, the promise of nothing, of no feeling=E2=80=A6<br>
And then a silver hare, a boar and a fox soared past Harry, Ron and Hermion=
e=E2=80=99s heads: the Dementors fell back before the creatures=E2=80=99 ap=
proach. Three more people had arrived out of the darkness to stand beside t=
hem, their wands outstretched, continuing to cast their Patronuses: Luna, E=
rnie and Seamus.
<br>
<em>Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows</em></p>
</blockquote>
